      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): hydrate allowlisted dynamic model metadata",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhat problem does this PR solve?\n\n- Fixes gateway/model catalog metadata for exact allowlisted dynamic models such as `ollama/minimax-m3:cloud`.\n- Full catalog loads now ask provider dynamic hooks to materialize exact `agents.defaults.models` refs that are missing from discovery, so live `/api/show` metadata can carry `reasoning: true` into catalog/thinking validation.\n\nWhy does this matter now?\n\n- Issue #90315 reports that local Ollama dynamic resolution accepts `--thinking low`, while the gateway path rejects the same model as off-only unless users duplicate metadata under `models.providers.ollama.models[]`.\n\nWhat is the intended outcome?\n\n- An exact allowlisted dynamic Ollama model can keep provider-discovered thinking metadata in the runtime catalog without adding manual provider model rows.\n- Existing discovered catalog entries remain available even if one dynamic allowlist metadata lookup fails.\n\nWhat is intentionally out of scope?\n\n- No new config, env var, migration, or Ollama-specific hardcoded model id.\n- No change to read-only catalog browse behavior; dynamic provider hooks still run only on full catalog loads.\n\nWhat does success look like?\n\n- Gateway thinking validation can see the same `reasoning: true` metadata that dynamic provider resolution discovers for an exact allowlisted model.\n\nWhat should reviewers focus on?\n\n- Whether full catalog load is the right owner boundary for materializing exact allowlisted dynamic model metadata.\n- Whether per-ref failure isolation is sufficient for transient provider/API failures.\n\n## Linked context\n\nWhich issue does this close?\n\nCloses #90315\n\nWhich issues, PRs, or discussions are related?\n\nRelated #90138, but that PR fixes MiniMax provider thinking behavior and does not touch the Ollama gateway catalog path.\n\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner?\n\nNo direct maintainer request; issue is labeled queueable/fix-shape-clear.\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- Behavior addressed: Exact allowlisted dynamic Ollama models can lose live-discovered `reasoning` metadata in the catalog path, making `--thinking low` fail as unsupported even though dynamic provider resolution can run the model.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw CLI from this branch on macOS, with an isolated `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH` / `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR` and a temporary local Ollama-compatible HTTP server. That server returned no `/api/tags` rows, then returned `/api/show` metadata for `minimax-m3:cloud` with `capabilities: [\"thinking\", \"tools\", \"completion\"]`, and finally returned a native Ollama `/api/chat` response.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  1. Start a local Ollama-compatible server on `127.0.0.1:<temp-port>`.\n  2. Write temporary config with only `agents.defaults.models[\"ollama/minimax-m3:cloud\"] = {}` and provider `models.providers.ollama.baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:<temp-port>`.\n  3. Run:\n     ```sh\n     OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-90315-proof-*/openclaw.json \\\n     OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=/tmp/openclaw-90315-proof-*/state \\\n     OLLAMA_API_KEY=ollama-local \\\n     pnpm openclaw infer model run --local \\\n       --model ollama/minimax-m3:cloud \\\n       --thinking low \\\n       --prompt \"Reply with exactly: pong\" \\\n       --json\n     ```\n- Evidence after fix (screenshot, recording, terminal capture, console output, redacted runtime log, linked artifact, or copied live output):\n  Terminal capture copied live output from `pnpm openclaw infer model run --local --model ollama/minimax-m3:cloud --thinking low --json`:\n\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"commandStatus\": 0,\n    \"run\": {\n      \"ok\": true,\n      \"capability\": \"model.run\",\n      \"transport\": \"local\",\n      \"provider\": \"ollama\",\n      \"model\": \"minimax-m3:cloud\",\n      \"attempts\": [],\n      \"outputs\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \"pong\",\n          \"mediaUrl\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    \"showBody\": {\n      \"name\": \"minimax-m3:cloud\"\n    },\n    \"chatBody\": {\n      \"model\": \"minimax-m3:cloud\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"user\",\n          \"content\": \"Reply with exactly: pong\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"stream\": true,\n      \"options\": {\n        \"num_predict\": 8192\n      }\n    },\n    \"requestUrls\": [\n      \"/api/tags\",\n      \"/api/show\",\n      \"/api/chat\"\n    ]\n  }\n  ```\n- Observed result after fix: The real CLI command accepted `--thinking low`, queried `/api/show` for the exact allowlisted `minimax-m3:cloud` model that was absent from `/api/tags`, called `/api/chat`, and returned `ok: true` with `pong` from the Ollama-compatible runtime path.\n- What was not tested: A live gateway inference against Ollama Cloud's real `minimax-m3:cloud` service was not completed from this machine.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: The local proof uses a local Ollama-compatible server rather than Ollama Cloud credentials. A direct gateway attempt against the same local server was tried, but the temporary gateway closed the WebSocket before the model run completed, so it is not claimed as passing proof here.\n- Before evidence (optional but encouraged): The issue includes the before failure: gateway rejects `--thinking low` with `Thinking level \"low\" is not supported for ollama/minimax-m3:cloud. Use one of: off.` when only `agents.defaults.models` contains the model.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\nWhich commands did you run?\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/model-catalog.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/ollama/index.test.ts extensions/ollama/src/provider-models.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/model-selection.test.ts src/auto-reply/thinking.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/model-catalog.test.ts extensions/ollama/index.test.ts extensions/ollama/src/provider-models.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/model-selection.test.ts src/auto-reply/thinking.test.ts`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check src/agents/model-catalog.ts src/agents/model-catalog.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check HEAD~1..HEAD`\n- `pnpm tsgo:prod`\n- `pnpm check:test-types`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode commit --commit HEAD`\n\nWhat regression coverage was added or updated?\n\n- `src/agents/model-catalog.test.ts` now covers exact allowlisted dynamic model metadata hydration, supported metadata preservation, per-ref failure isolation, retry after partial hydration failure, and cacheable-required caller isolation.\n\nWhat failed before this fix, if known?\n\n- Source path analysis showed exact allowlist rows missing from catalog could fall back to synthetic provider/id-only metadata, leaving thinking validation off-only.\n\nIf no test was added, why not?\n\n- Regression tests were added.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nYes.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nNo.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nNo new auth or secret surfaces. Full catalog loads may call existing provider dynamic model hooks for exact configured model refs; read-only browse paths remain side-effect-free.\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n\nFull model catalog loads now perform optional dynamic metadata hydration for exact allowlisted refs.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n\nThe behavior is limited to non-read-only catalog loads, skips refs already present, uses existing provider dynamic hooks, and isolates failures per ref so base catalog entries and other dynamic refs remain available.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n\nMaintainer review.\n\nWhat is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?\n\nCI and maintainer review. A maintainer or reporter with Ollama Cloud credentials can add true end-to-end gateway proof for `minimax-m3:cloud`.\n\nWhich bot or reviewer comments were addressed?\n\n- Local autoreview initially found failure-isolation, metadata-preservation, and cacheability race issues; these were fixed before this update. The final autoreview run was clean.\n\n\n\n",
